               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1003" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1003" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1003" type="surname" value="LINE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1003" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES LINE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, N</hi> 282.) In consequence of information, and receiving this duplicate (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) from a man named Cole, I went to Mr. Cockburn, pawnbroker, at Richmond—I produced the duplicate, and was shown a gown—I received a description of the person who had pledged it; and in consequence found the prisoner—I asked him if he had lost a duplicate; he said "No"—I showed him this ticket, and said, "Do you know anything about this?"—he said, "No"—I asked him to go to a public-house with me, and he refused—I asked him where he was the day this property was pledged; he said he should not tell me—as we were going to the station, I saw his hand in his pocket—I had a struggle with him, and in his hand I found a duplicate for two blankets, and at the station I found another duplicate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1004" type="witnessName">
